3H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 2, nRot: 0, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "0678a036f8a9c4fb04ddd90b509e321b029bb55ff06112389d5c3e8abb0d1e96"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/weak_twos"]
[Student "S"]
{NORTH may have an opening hand, but it is just the wrong kind of hand to respond to 
partner's preemptive bid. She doesn't have the immediate winners that SOUTH is likely 
to need, but she is in good shape for defense should the opponents bid.

In other words, NORTH has the perfect hand with which to pass.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "E:54.863.AKQ974.85 T98732.J54.82.J9 KQJ.AK7.J63.AK42 A6.QT92.T5.QT763"]
[Declarer "W"]
[Contract "6NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
2D pass 2NT pass 3NT pass 6NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 2, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "a24da5119fca54701ebcf38208db8721075eba24cd7fe7745a2037a8ad56c0ca"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/weak_twos"]
[Student "S"]
{The 2NT response to a Weak Two opening is a wonderful tool. You can learn a lot about 
partner's hand and you are absolutely certain that it will not be passed out.

In this Deal WEST has a huge hand and EAST opens 2\D. 
There are a lot of approaches WEST might try, but the simplest is to start with 2NT.

When EAST shows \D A K Q x x x WEST has an easy 6NT bid.}

